  "Thermal pollution from power plants": "",
  "Cultural eutrophication is caused by excessive nutrient inputs (nitrogen and phosphorus) from human activities such as agriculture, sewage discharge, and urban runoff, which stimulate excessive algal growth in water bodies.": "",
  "What sequence of events leads to a dead zone in a water body?": "",
  "Oil spill → chemical contamination → fish death": "",
  "Temperature rise → evaporation → salt concentration → organism death": "",
  "Excess nutrients → algal bloom → algae die-off → bacterial decomposition → oxygen depletion": "",
  "Acid rain → pH drop → chemical reactions → toxin release": "",
  "Dead zones form through a cascade: excess nutrients fuel algal blooms, the algae eventually die, decomposing bacteria consume dissolved oxygen as they break down the dead algae, creating hypoxic conditions that kill or drive away marine life.": "",
