  "There is no connection between Midwest farming and Gulf fishing": "",
  "Midwest farms compete with the fishing industry for labor": "",
  "This illustrates a distant cause-and-effect: nutrient runoff from Midwest agriculture travels through the Mississippi watershed to the Gulf, creating dead zones that reduce shrimp habitat and force fishers to travel farther, increasing costs.": "",
  "A city discharges treated wastewater with reduced but still significant phosphorus levels into a small lake. Despite upgrading the treatment plant, the lake continues to experience algal blooms. What might explain the persistent problem?": "",
