  "Internal phosphorus loading occurs when phosphorus that accumulated in lake sediments during years of pollution is released back into the water column under certain conditions (low oxygen, high pH), sustaining eutrophication even after external inputs decrease.": "",
  "A coastal community bans phosphorus-containing lawn fertilizers and detergents. After several years, the local bay shows some improvement in water clarity but algal blooms persist. Soil testing of surrounding farmland shows high phosphorus levels. What does this suggest?": "",
