  "Phosphorus from detergents was never a real problem": "",
  "While the urban phosphorus ban helped, agricultural runoff from phosphorus-saturated soils continues to deliver significant nutrient loads. Effective eutrophication management requires addressing all major sources including agricultural nonpoint pollution.": "",
  "Scientists propose using constructed wetlands to intercept agricultural drainage before it reaches a lake. How would wetlands help reduce eutrophication?": "",
